# TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (TRD)

## 1. Document Overview

### 1.1 Purpose
This Technical Requirements Document (TRD) translates the Functional Requirements Document (FRD) into detailed technical specifications for implementing an AWS Glue-based data processing pipeline. This document provides implementation-ready technical design for ingesting customer and order data from S3, performing data quality operations, implementing SCD Type 2 logic using Apache Hudi, and generating aggregated analytics tables.

### 1.2 Scope
This TRD covers the technical implementation of:
- AWS Glue ETL jobs for reading CSV files from S3 source locations
- Data quality transformations including null removal and deduplication using PySpark
- AWS Glue Data Catalog table registration for all processed datasets
- SCD Type 2 implementation using Apache Hudi framework for order summary table
- Incremental processing logic for customer update detection and propagation
- Aggregation logic for customer spend analytics
- Error handling, validation rules, and operational parameters for AWS Glue execution
- Schema definitions and ETL mappings for all data flows

