### **TR-INGEST-001: Implement Customer Data Ingestion from S3**
- **FR Reference**: FR-INGEST-001
- **Objective**: Read customer CSV files from S3 source location and load into Spark DataFrame for downstream processing
- **Source Details**: 
  - Source Path: `s3://adif-sdlc/sdlc_wizard/customerdata/`
  - Source Format: CSV
  - Source Type: Raw files
- **Target Details**: In-memory Spark DataFrame (intermediate processing object)
- **Schema**: 
  ```
  CustId: String (inferred from CSV)
  Name: String (inferred from CSV)
  EmailId: String (inferred from CSV)
  Region: String (inferred from CSV)
  ```
  Note: Data types not specified in FRD; String type assumed for CSV ingestion
- **Transformation Logic**:
  - Use Spark CSV reader with header=true option
  - Read all CSV files matching pattern in source path using wildcard or recursive read
  - Parse header row containing: CustId, Name, EmailId, Region
  - Load into DataFrame with schema inference or explicit schema definition
  - No transformations applied at ingestion stage
- **Validation Rules**:
  - Verify source path exists and is accessible
  - Verify CSV files contain header row with expected column names: CustId, Name, EmailId, Region
  - Verify at least one CSV file exists in source location
  - Validate CSV structure is parseable by Spark CSV reader
- **Error Handling**:
  - If source path does not exist: Raise exception and fail job with error message "Source path not found: s3://adif-sdlc/sdlc_wizard/customerdata/"
  - If CSV files are malformed: Log malformed records to CloudWatch and raise exception with details
  - If required columns are missing: Raise exception with error message "Schema mismatch: Expected columns [CustId, Name, EmailId, Region]"
  - If no files found in source path: Raise exception "No CSV files found in source location"
- **Runtime Parameters**:
  - `source_customer_path`: s3://adif-sdlc/sdlc_wizard/customerdata/
  - `csv_header`: true
  - `csv_inferSchema`: true (or explicit schema definition)
  - `csv_delimiter`: , (comma - standard CSV)
- **Operational Notes**:
  - Ensure Glue job IAM role has s3:GetObject permission on source bucket
  - Monitor CloudWatch logs for read errors or schema mismatches
  - Consider enabling Glue job bookmark if incremental file processing is required (not specified in FRD)

