### **TR-CLEAN-001: Implement Null Value Removal Transformation**
- **FR Reference**: FR-CLEAN-001
- **Objective**: Remove records containing string "Null" or actual NULL values from customer and order DataFrames
- **Source Details**: 
  - Customer DataFrame from TR-INGEST-001 (in-memory)
  - Order DataFrame from TR-INGEST-002 (in-memory)
- **Target Details**: 
  - Cleaned Customer DataFrame (in-memory)
  - Cleaned Order DataFrame (in-memory)
- **Schema**: 
  - Customer: CustId, Name, EmailId, Region (unchanged from source)
  - Order: OrderId, ItemName, PricePerUnit, Qty, Date, CustId (unchanged from source)
- **Transformation Logic**:
  - For Customer DataFrame:
    - Filter out rows where any column contains string value "Null" (case-sensitive match)
    - Filter out rows where any column contains actual NULL value (isNull() check)
    - Apply filter conditions: `(col("CustId") != "Null") & (col("Name") != "Null") & (col("EmailId") != "Null") & (col("Region") != "Null")`
    - Apply null check: `col("CustId").isNotNull() & col("Name").isNotNull() & col("EmailId").isNotNull() & col("Region").isNotNull()`
  - For Order DataFrame:
    - Filter out rows where any column contains string value "Null" (case-sensitive match)
    - Filter out rows where any column contains actual NULL value (isNull() check)
    - Apply filter conditions: `(col("OrderId") != "Null") & (col("ItemName") != "Null") & (col("PricePerUnit") != "Null") & (col("Qty") != "Null") & (col("Date") != "Null") & (col("CustId") != "Null")`
    - Apply null check: `col("OrderId").isNotNull() & col("ItemName").isNotNull() & col("PricePerUnit").isNotNull() & col("Qty").isNotNull() & col("Date").isNotNull() & col("CustId").isNotNull()`
  - Process each DataFrame independently
- **Validation Rules**:
  - Verify input DataFrames are not empty before applying filters
  - Log count of records removed due to "Null" string values
  - Log count of records removed due to NULL values
  - Verify output DataFrames contain no "Null" strings or NULL values in any column
- **Error Handling**:
  - If input DataFrame is empty: Log warning to CloudWatch and proceed with empty DataFrame
  - If all records are filtered out: Log warning "All records removed during null cleaning" and proceed with empty DataFrame
  - Error handling not specified in FRD for other scenarios
- **Runtime Parameters**:
  - `null_string_value`: "Null" (case-sensitive)
  - `log_removed_records`: true (for monitoring)
- **Operational Notes**:
  - Monitor CloudWatch metrics for percentage of records removed
  - High removal rates may indicate data quality issues in source systems
  - Consider implementing data quality alerts if removal rate exceeds threshold (not specified in FRD)

