  - For Customer DataFrame:
    - Apply Spark `dropDuplicates()` function on all columns
    - Retain first occurrence of duplicate record (Spark default behavior)
    - Deduplication based on exact match across all columns: CustId, Name, EmailId, Region
  - For Order DataFrame:
    - Apply Spark `dropDuplicates()` function on all columns
    - Retain first occurrence of duplicate record (Spark default behavior)
